Module 85
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 7 — Procedural Memory & Public Archive
Module 85 – Public Docket Mirrors: Screenshot, Save, Cite 🪞📜
⚖️ Core Message
If the docket is the memory, mirror it. Regularly capture PDFs and screenshots of the docket and key entries so changes are visible and provable.

📖 Lesson Content
• Cadence — Weekly PDF of docket; screenshots on major changes.
• Proof — Timestamp + hash every capture; store in /Public/Docket and /Restricted/Originals.
• Cites — 'Dkt (captured 2025‑09‑01, SHA‑256 3f2c…) at Entry 51'.
• Diffs — Before/after images to show edits, seals, or deletions.
• Court Use — Attach as exhibits in Notices of Docket Change.
📝 Assignment
Create a 'Docket Mirror' folder with the latest PDF, three screenshots, and a short declaration authenticating capture method and hash.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
DECLARATION (Docket Mirror)
I captured the docket on 09/01 at 09:03 using [tool]. The PDF and PNGs' SHA‑256 values are listed in Ex. A.

💡 Reflection
A mirrored docket is a guardrail against accidental memory loss.

🎨 Visual Pairing
Side‑by‑side 'Docket v1' and 'Docket v2' with a small hash tag below.



