Module 89
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 7 — Procedural Memory & Public Archive
Module 89 – Image & PDF Authenticity: EXIF, Hashes, and Chain 🖼️🔒
⚖️ Core Message
Images and PDFs carry metadata. Preserve EXIF where appropriate, compute hashes, and declare chain of custody so exhibits can be trusted.

📖 Lesson Content
• EXIF — Capture and export with minimal edits; note tools used.
• Hash — SHA‑256 for each file; list values in manifest and briefs.
• Chain — Who captured, when, where; who stored; any edits annotated.
• Redaction — Produce redacted and original; keep originals restricted.
• Declaration — Short custodian statement for each key image/PDF.
📝 Assignment
Create an 'Authenticity Pack' for two exhibits: EXIF printout, hash manifest, and a custodian declaration.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
DECLARATION (Custodian)
I captured Ex. P on 08/10 with [device/app]; SHA‑256 'a1b9…'; original stored in /Restricted/Originals.

💡 Reflection
Authenticity earns trust; trust earns leverage.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A photo icon with a small 'EXIF' tag and a hash string.



