Module 90
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 7 — Procedural Memory & Public Archive
Module 90 – Public Comment Windows: Influence Without Overreach 🗳️📝
⚖️ Core Message
When agencies or courts invite comment (rules, forms), submit brief, evidence‑backed statements that point to your archive—not your feelings.

📖 Lesson Content
• Scope — Address the docketing/form/process issue, not general grievances.
• Evidence — Cite your Top‑10 with hashes; summarize impact briefly.
• Ask — Propose concrete language (e.g., deficiency order requirements).
• Tone — Neutral, specific, respectful; avoid speculation.
• Publication — Mirror your comment in your archive with links.
📝 Assignment
Write a 1‑page public comment proposing one process fix and citing two exhibits (with hashes).

✅ Model Answer (Template)
COMMENT (EXCERPT)
We propose adding: 'Clerks shall issue a deficiency order specifying cure and rule cite within 3 days.'

💡 Reflection
Well‑aimed comments turn private pain into public process.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A small rules paragraph with a pencil edit showing added language.



