Module 92
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 7 — Procedural Memory & Public Archive
Module 92 – Reproducible Research: From Claims to Notebooks 📓🧪
⚖️ Core Message
Treat your record like a dataset. Release CSVs and small scripts/notebooks that reproduce your charts and metrics.

📖 Lesson Content
• Data — CSVs for events, latencies, outcomes; link to sources.
• Code — Simple scripts (no secrets) to compute KPIs and draw charts.
• Docs — README with steps to reproduce; versions; hashes of outputs.
• Cite — Include DOIs or permalinks for datasets if possible.
• Privacy — Anonymize; aggregate where necessary.
📝 Assignment
Publish a 'reproducible' folder with one CSV, one script/notebook, and a README that recreates a chart used in your filing.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
README: 'Run notebook.ipynb to produce telemetry.png from events.csv; verify hashes listed in manifest.txt.'

💡 Reflection
Reproducibility converts narrative into evidence others can extend.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A notebook icon pointing to a small chart with a 'reproduce' arrow.



