Module 93
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 7 — Procedural Memory & Public Archive
Module 93 – Governance in the Open: Issues, PRs, and Releases 🧑‍💻📦
⚖️ Core Message
Borrow from open‑source. Use issues to track work, pull‑requests for edits, and releases for freezing public versions of your archive.

📖 Lesson Content
• Issues — 'Good first issue' labels; checklists; clear acceptance criteria.
• PRs — Proposed changes reviewed by a second person; small diffs preferred.
• Releases — Tag versions; attach Top‑10 and manifest; changelog entry.
• Security — Triage sensitive items in private; publish redacted outcomes.
• Community — Code of conduct; contributor guide; license file.
📝 Assignment
Create an 'Issues & Releases' workflow note and publish a v1.0.0 release of your Top‑10 + manifest.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
RELEASE NOTE (EXCERPT)
v1.0.0 — Initial public release; Top‑10.pdf (bookmarked); index.csv (hashes); corrections policy.

💡 Reflection
Governance signals seriousness and invites safe collaboration.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A 'tag' icon labeled v1.0.0 next to an issues list.



