Module 95 – Appeals Tracking: Longitudinal Memory Across Courts 🧭📊
⚖️ Core Message
Track cases across trial and appeals with one table so everyone sees posture, standards, and next dates in one place.

📖 Lesson Content
• Table — Columns: Court, Case #, Issue, Standard, Status, Next Date, Links.
• Cross‑Refs — Link to Top‑10 and major orders.
• Calendar — Auto‑pull next dates into your main calendar.
• Updates — Monthly check; post notable changes.
• Public View — Publish a redacted version for coalition visibility.
📝 Assignment
Build an Appeals Tracker table and add two matters; publish a redacted view and link in your README.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
APPEALS ROW
Court: 9th Cir; Issue: findings; Standard: abuse; Status: briefing; Next: 10/15.

💡 Reflection
A clear map reduces confusion and duplicated effort.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A compass icon next to a small tracker table.



