Module 96
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 7 — Procedural Memory & Public Archive
Module 96 – Record Compression: Summaries that Don’t Lose the Thread 🧵📦
⚖️ Core Message
Compress without distortion. Summaries should cite every key point and link to full exhibits; use consistent headings.

📖 Lesson Content
• Headings — Problem • Evidence • Standard • Ask.
• Density — Short paragraphs; keep numbers and cites intact.
• Cross‑Links — Every claim points to exhibit/ECF; add hash.
• Variants — 150‑word, one‑pager, and two‑pager versions.
• QA — Have someone verify cites before release.
📝 Assignment
Write a 150‑word summary and a one‑pager of the same issue; include pin‑cites and hashes.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
150 WORDS (EXCERPT)
Three timely tenders, no deficiency order; we ask for nunc pro tunc acceptance…

💡 Reflection
Compression earns attention; citations earn trust.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A large stack of pages squeezed into a neat one‑pager with citations preserved.



