Module 97
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 7 — Procedural Memory & Public Archive
Module 97 – Pattern Synthesis: Multi‑Case Signals Without Overclaiming 📡🔬
⚖️ Core Message
Use multiple matters to show patterns, but avoid overreach: cite specifics, annotate differences, and present signals, not verdicts.

📖 Lesson Content
• Signals — Shared delays/refusals/findings gaps across matters.
• Differences — Note distinct facts; don’t force equivalence.
• Graphics — Heatmaps/timelines; careful legends.
• Cites — Exhibit‑level citations for each matter.
• Language — 'Suggests a pattern' > 'Proves corruption'.
📝 Assignment
Create a two‑case comparison chart with signals and differences; write neutral captions with cites.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
CAPTION: 'Both matters show >14‑day latency to deficiency order (Ex. A; Ex. F); facts otherwise differ.'

💡 Reflection
Synthesis should invite inquiry, not foreclose it.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A small heatmap showing delays across two case rows and time columns.



