Module 98
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 7 — Procedural Memory & Public Archive
Module 98 – Open Dataset Release: Licenses, Readmes, and Limits 📂🔓
⚖️ Core Message
If you publish data, publish responsibly: explain scope, methods, and limits; pick a license; and invite replication.

📖 Lesson Content
• License — Open data license with attribution; exclude restricted items.
• README — Scope, definitions, methods, limitations, contact.
• Versioning — Tag releases; keep changelog.
• Consent — Remove PII/PHI; log removals.
• Cite — Provide a preferred citation for reuse.
📝 Assignment
Release a 'v1' dataset folder with LICENSE, README, data.csv, and a CHANGES.txt.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
CITATION
Mayron, C. (2025). Legal Calculus Dataset v1. DOI/URL.

💡 Reflection
Open data invites allies and scrutiny—the twin engines of progress.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A folder icon stamped 'v1' with files LICENSE/README/data.csv/CHANGES.



