Module 99
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 7 — Procedural Memory & Public Archive
Module 99 – Ethics Advisory: Boundaries for Public Memory 🧠⚖️
⚖️ Core Message
Build an informal advisory layer—law/ethics/media—so tough calls get second looks before publishing.

📖 Lesson Content
• Advisors — Mix legal, ethics, media literacy; document advice briefly.
• Process — Send a short memo with options and a recommended path.
• Conflicts — Recuse where needed; be transparent about limits.
• Storage — Keep advisory notes restricted; publish outcomes, not deliberations.
• Review — Quarterly check‑in on standards and edge cases.
📝 Assignment
Draft a one‑page 'Advisory Memo' for a tricky publishing decision; log the outcome in your privacy/corrections index.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
ADVISORY MEMO (EXCERPT)
Option A (publish redacted)… Option B (delay/seek consent)… Rec: A.

💡 Reflection
Advisory processes protect people—and your mission.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A lightbulb over a small scale icon; caption 'Advice received; path chosen.'



