Module 100
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 7 — Procedural Memory & Public Archive
Module 100 – Archive to Institution: From Personal Fight to Public Resource 🏛️📦
⚖️ Core Message
The end‑state of procedural memory is institutional: a resource library others can rely on long after your case ends.

📖 Lesson Content
• Partners — Libraries, clinics, justice tech labs; pick stable hosts.
• Packaging — Final Top‑50 exhibits; teaching pack; dataset; governance note.
• Metadata — DOIs/permalinks; catalog entries; author/date/version.
• Handoff — MOU for maintenance; update cadence; contact point.
• Announcement — Public note: what’s included, how to verify, how to extend.
📝 Assignment
Prepare an 'Institution Pack' folder (Top‑50, Education Pack, Dataset v1, Governance.md) and a 1‑page MOU draft with a host institution.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
MOU (EXCERPT)
Host preserves public files; updates quarterly; issues errata; attribution as 'Legal Calculus Archive'.

💡 Reflection
When memory becomes an institution, procedural justice scales.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A library building icon receiving a labeled archive box.

